Trucks have been targets for looting and burning in the protests that began on Friday. Sally Burdett speaks to Patrick O’Leary, he is the editor of FleetWatch magazine. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The Sapref oil refinery has declared a force majeure on contracts and is shutting down operations over ongoing violence. The Durban-based refinery is the biggest in Southern Africa and accounts for a third of the country's fuel supply. READ: COVID-19 vaccinations face delay after pharmacy lootings At the same, Fleetwatch Truck Magazine's Patrick O'Leary says the impact of the burning and looting of trucks has not even begun to be felt. He says that all products that need to be replaced will have to be moved by truck too, which will take a very long time.